Issue 215 | The New Aesthetic – Art From The Outer Limits

Alongside an illuminating, inspiring interview with 91-year-old fashion muse Iris Apfel by Karley Sciortino and photoshoot by Jeff Bark and styled by Dazed's Robbie Spencer is the scoop on Fatima Al-Qadiri's jaw-droppingly brutal imagining of Gulf futurism. Rounding up our issue on art's outer edge is a chat between Philip Glass and Beck on their collaborative remix project and Francesca Gavin's identification of the Off Modernists, plus six original artworks by this thrilling new breed.

Ghesquière's vision as seen by Dazed, as we delve through archive magazine editorial

of Nicolas Ghesquière's runway looks for Balenciaga, celebrating their favourite top-to-toe outfits as proposed by the designer. Now we delve into the Dazed archive to see Ghesquière's clothes as interpreted by the magazine's stylists over the years, from Katie England and Cathy Edwards to current senior contributing fashion editor Katie Shillingford and fashion director Karen Langley. This is an anthology of the avantgarde.
